{
  "texts": [
    "Second, cutting-edge computer chips, i.e.",
    "chips over a certain capability threshold, could be tracked, and governments could require a license to bring together large numbers of them.I estimate that these two policy proposals have a high chance of success, i.e. implementation.",
    "In contrast to halting or slowing AI research, they are compatible with commercial, military and other incentives which favor fast AI development.",
    "Moreover, since the number of hardware chips can be measured and tracked precisely, these policies can be operationalized well.The approach is moderately beneficent.",
    "It represents an important angle to regulate AI in the medium-term."
  ]
}